// lines starting with / are comments
// settings have a name followed by = followed by the value spaces are not allowed on a line.

// wifi router name
WIFI_SSID=write_here

// Wifi password
WIFI_PASSWORD=write_here

// change for your reagan and tariff. this can be found in your Octopus account on there web site
OCTOPUS_URL=https://api.octopus.energy/v1/products/AGILE-FLEX-22-11-25/electricity-tariffs/E-1R-AGILE-FLEX-22-11-25-J/standard-unit-rates/

// api call to get wether forecast. only change the latitude and latitude in this to match your location. This can be done by visiting the site in a web browser
WETHER_URL=https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=51.003293&longitude=0.396079&daily=apparent_temperature_max,apparent_temperature_min,sunshine_duration&forecast_days=3


// Battery extend and Battery save allow power to be drawn from the grid instead of the battery when the price is less than the set values.
// The set values are modified as SOC falls up to x2 at 20% soc. i.e. if the battery is running out of power power will be purchased up to 2x the set value.
// In battery save mode power will always be drawn from the grid if not provided by the solar panels.
// Execs power from the solar panels will still charge the battery.
PRICE_LOW_ALLOW_BATTERY_SAVE=10 

// Battery extend allows a small amount of power to be purchased but will still supply large loads from the battery.
// This is done to save the invertor working inefficiently to supply the background load.
PRICE_LOW_ALLOW_BATTERY_EXTEND=15

// If price is less than this then allow more power to be stored than required for today.
PRICE_LOW_INCREASE_CHARGING_TIME=9 

// the capacity of the battery in W
BATTERY_SIZE 11900.0

// efficiency of inverter ie 1KW in 0.84KW
BATTERY_EFF=84.0 

// If you have electrical heating The power use is heavily dependent on outside temperature. This value modifies 
// the required_power = required_power + (deltaT * TEMPERATURE_COMPENSATION). Set to zero to disable                         
TEMPERATURE_COMPENSATION=220
 
// SOLAR_PANEL_COFF is multiplied by the forecast solar radiation for 1m squared. To get this value use number of m sq solar panels/ panel efficiency ()
// eg 4m sq of solar panels with 12% efficiency would be 4/12 = 0.33. To play safe when the forecast is not good you can make this number smaller
// if too big you may run out of power at peak time. If to low you may reach 100% charge and export to grid having bought too much power the night before.                                  
SOLAR_PANEL_COFF=0.8 

// LOG_DATA selects if anything should be logged and to where 
LOG_DATA=2

// It is possible to log data into google spread sheets. To do this you have to generate the following line using google script files.
DATA_TO_SS=https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbyufeQCFAvoOzhuiEZw0fGEf0NNo_0-t7f5ZgHkvI1ymZ5vtVDKWg7v3h3SFcRoJMkGhQ/exec?temperature=20.00&humidity=1.00

//end line 50
